---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Abby | Chaos With Clarity" description="9 years finance: EY to fractional CFO. Poet, founder, and soul worker.">

  <!-- PAGE HEADER -->
  <div class="pt-32 pb-12 px-6 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="w-px h-12 bg-cwc-border mb-8"></div>
    <p class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-cwc-muted mb-3">The Person</p>
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-6xl text-cwc-text">About Abby</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pb-24">

    <!-- ABOUT GRID -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-cwc-border mb-20 reveal">

      <!-- Photo col -->
      <div class="bg-cwc-surface flex flex-col">
        <!-- Replace with your actual photo -->
        <div class="aspect-[4/5] bg-cwc-surface-2 flex items-center justify-center border-b border-cwc-border">
          <div class="text-center">
            <i class="ph ph-user-circle text-6xl text-cwc-border"></i>
            <p class="text-cwc-muted/40 text-xs mt-3">Your photo here<br/>images/about.jpg</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-8">
          <blockquote class="font-serif italic text-cwc-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
            "Spreadsheets couldn't answer the chest ache. So I write."
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Text col -->
      <div class="bg-cwc-bg p-8 md:p-12 flex flex-col justify-center gap-6">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-cwc-muted leading-relaxed">
          <p class="font-serif text-xl text-cwc-text">
            9 years in finance: EY to fractional CFO for founders.
          </p>
          <p>Spreadsheets couldn't answer the chest ache.</p>
          <p>So I write: money as fuel, death as teacher, freedom as breath.</p>
          <p>
            <strong class="text-cwc-text font-medium">Chaos With Clarity</strong>
            = numbers + soul + raw.
          </p>
          <p>Not therapy. Not coaching. A mirror. A pause.</p>
          <p>
            If you're a founder caught between ambition and peace —
            if the numbers are good but something still feels wrong —
            let's talk.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="font-serif italic text-cwc-accent text-lg">– Abby</p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-2">
          <a href="/offerings"
             class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase bg-cwc-accent text-cwc-bg px-6 py-2.5 hover:bg-cwc-accent-dark transition-colors">
            Work with Me
          </a>
          <a href="/writings"
             class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase border border-cwc-border text-cwc-muted px-6 py-2.5 hover:border-cwc-accent hover:text-cwc-accent transition-all duration-200">
            Read My Poems
          </a>
        </div>

        <p class="text-cwc-muted/50 text-xs mt-2">
          Looking for the CFO work?
          <a href="https://abbyjain.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-cwc-accent/70 hover:text-cwc-accent transition-colors ml-1">
            abbyjain.com ↗
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- LONGER STORY -->
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto reveal">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-10">
        <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-cwc-accent"></div>
        <h2 class="font-serif italic text-cwc-muted text-xl">The longer story</h2>
        <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-cwc-border"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 text-cwc-muted leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          I started writing because the spreadsheets stopped making sense.
          Not financially — the numbers were always there. But existentially.
          You can model a company's runway to the day. You cannot model
          why you lie awake at 2am wondering if any of it means anything.
        </p>
        <p>
          Nine years of finance — from audit rooms at EY to sitting across
          from founders who had everything and felt nothing — taught me one thing:
          clarity without depth is just noise with good formatting.
        </p>
        <p>
          The poems started in a notebook. Then they started helping people.
          Not because they had answers, but because they named things that
          people had been carrying silently.
        </p>
        <p>
          Chaos With Clarity is where I bring both sides together.
          The CFO who can read your runway and the poet who can sit with
          what the runway is actually for.
        </p>
        <p>
          If that's the conversation you've been looking for — you're in the right place.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- JOIN STRIP -->
    <div class="border-t border-cwc-border mt-20 pt-12 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6 reveal">
      <p class="font-serif italic text-cwc-muted">Poems. Reflections. Circles. Inbox only.</p>
      <a href="/join"
         class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase bg-cwc-accent text-cwc-bg px-8 py-3 hover:bg-cwc-accent-dark transition-colors whitespace-nowrap">
        Join the Chaos
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
